So far the outlook is bleak. I talked to several zope-gurus at Pycon and no one has come up with a valid approach for doing this aside from monkey patching the `__iro__` attribute onto the classes. For example,

```python
class LoginService(object):
    pass

def register_factory(factory, iface):
    if not IInterface.providedBy(iface):
        iface.__iro__ = (iface,)

register_factory(None, iface=LoginService)
```

Another option is to dynamically generate appropriate interfaces for every class in the `__mro__`. This is hairy to do correctly though. Both approaches require some unhappy assumptions about what objects are used on the flip side for `find_service`.

